--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
filesdir-check 1.0 : 2010-12-07
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - Rewrote the program in python. (It used to be a bash script)
 - Added basic command-line options: --verbose, --version, --help
 - Fixed handling directories in $FILESDIR: they are now recursed
 - Renamed the program to filesdir-check. The python module is filesdir_check
 - Started using git for version control. Prior to this there was no version
   control! The repository is available at github.com/jalan

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
file_hunter 0.2 : 2010-11-12
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - Removed the check for empty file directories. Since I didn't find any, I
   think something further upstream already prevents that problem
 - Renamed variables to be more in line with the usual portage terminology
 - Strip all quotation marks from ebuilds. Now we catch things like this:
     epatch "${FILESDIR}/${P}"-gentoo.patch
   This change dropped about 150 false positives

